    "talking_points": "**Mindset** \u2014 This is our tournament debut and we're here to make a statement. We've earned our #18 ranking through hard work and smart hockey, so let's come out with confidence and play our game from the opening faceoff.\n\n**Discipline** \u2014 We've stayed clean so far with zero penalty minutes, and that discipline needs to continue. Smart, physical play without taking unnecessary penalties will give us the best chance to control this game and stay out of trouble.\n\n**The Opponent** \u2014 Ennismore is ranked #25 but they're here for a reason, and every team at provincials can play. They'll be hungry to prove themselves against a higher-ranked team like us, so we need to match their intensity and impose our style early.\n\n**What We Need** \u2014 Only pool winners advance, so every single point matters. We need to play a complete 60 minutes, support each other through all three zones, and execute the systems we've worked on all season to get that crucial first win.",
